# mattpocock skills bundle — installed via `npx skills add mattpocock/skills`,
# symlinked into .claude/skills/. Not committed: each teammate runs `npx skills`
# locally to get the current version they prefer.
.agents/
# npx skills installer also drops symlinks into ./skills/<name> pointing at
# ../.agents/skills/<name>. Symlinks would be broken on any clone. Only the
# AutoViral skill itself (skills/autoviral/) stays committed.
skills/*
!skills/autoviral
skills-lock.json
# Electron desktop shell build artifacts — compiled main, staged native
# toolchain (chromium / ffmpeg / pre-built remotion bundle), and packaged
# installers. Source (desktop/*.ts, *.yml, tsconfig) IS committed.
desktop/out/
desktop/release/
desktop/build-resources/
# Local issue tracker stand-in — `to-issues` breakdown of a PRD into
# tracer-bullet slices, kept as local working files until `gh` is available
# to publish them as real GitHub Issues. Canonical source is the PRD in
# docs/prd/ (committed); these slice files are transient local state.
docs/issues/
